questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: These plasmids do not contain DNA.
questions.explanation: False. Plasmids are small, circular, double-stranded DNA molecules that are distinct from a cell's chromosomal DNA.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: Binary fission of prokaryotes is not at all similar to the the cell cycle of eukaryotes.
questions.explanation: False. While there are significant differences (e.g., prokaryotes lack a nucleus and mitosis), both processes involve DNA replication and segregation of genetic material into two daughter cells.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: The arrow is representing a new cell membrane & cell wall.
questions.explanation: True. During binary fission, a new cell wall and cell membrane (the septum) forms to divide the parent cell into two daughter cells.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: Under ideal conditions, some bacteria can divide every 20 minutes.
questions.explanation: True. This rapid exponential growth is characteristic of many bacterial species, such as E. coli, in optimal environments.

questions.subject: Microbiology
questions.question: How many bacterial cells will be produced after 3 hours?
questions.explanation: Assuming a division time of 30 minutes, in 3 hours (180 minutes) there would be 6 divisions (180/30=6). This results in 2^6 = 64 cells. If the division time was 20 minutes as stated in the previous question, the answer would be 512.
